OL,2,MLights, Spectrometer, Action!
OL,4,CRobin Wilson
OL,5,CSun 14:30-15:10
OL,6,CStage C
OL,8,GCome and watch me point a spectrometer
OL,9,Gat a load of things, and teach you
OL,10,Gabout how light interacts with stuff.
OL,11,GWhat’s a spectrometer, you ask? Well
OL,12,Git’s a device that measures light and
OL,13,Gproduces a graph of the brightness of
OL,14,Gthe light at each wavelength. I
OL,15,Ginherited one last year, and this talk
OL,16,Gwill mainly consist of live demos of
OL,17,Gthe spectrometer, along with
OL,18,Gexplanations of what we’re seeing and
OL,19,Ghow it works. The talk will be
OL,20,Gaccessible to almost anyone - you
OL,22,D]CEMFFAX: The world at your fingertips\
